{
  "texts": [
    "Wang et al. [38] proposed Shapley Explanation Networks (SHAPNETs), which leverages Shapley values as a latent representation for deep models, enabling hierarchical explanations and explanation regularization.",
    "Ts efficiently compute explanations during training and testing by providing hierarchical explanations during the forward propagation process.In model-agnostic approximate methods, Kernel SHAP [14] is currently widely used.",
    "For tree and neural network models, TreeSHAP [35,36] and DeepSHAP [14] are more applicable.",
    "All of these methods are integrated in the SHAP library, available at: https://github.com/shap/shap.",
    "Overall, compared to model-agnostic methods, modelspecific approximations of Shapley value have greatly improved computational efficiency but lack flexibility."
  ]
}